divs: Sighting DetailsI was driving southbound on the FL Turnpike passing through West Palm Beach. on my way to work.I'm not sure of the year, but it was between 2000 and 2005. It was approximately 06:05 to 06:15, before sunrise. The morning was overcast with low-lying clouds. I saw above me, just at the bottom edge of a low cloud, a green steady light, cigar-shaped with rounded ends. It was a soft, steady light and remained for about 7 secs before disappearing into the cloud. The light did not flash or strobe. To compare with a field of vision, if you hold up a typical pen at arms length, only about half the length of the pen, would equate with the size of the light. It was the shape, color, and non-strobing that caught my eye. I was curious, but not frightened. The Palm Beach airport is near the location. I reported this when it happened to another UFO site, but lost the web address.
Summary: Green light cigar-shaped but with rounded ends
